From brown ftms UUCP Vidiot Subject Re viewing postscript files under X windows In article gordons mon Gordon Sasamori writes In C tGoJ J inmet camb inmet com George Snyder writes In article sk rINN Kin Cho writes I wonder if anybody know of a X window based postscript file viewer that runs under SunOS prefered , HPUX, or IBM AIX If you are running Sun OpenWindows, you can use pageview This is an X Window PostScript previewer like ghostview , but displays much nicer Yes, but it's broken on OW It does not handle multiple pages well If you don't have the proper PostScript commands it will draw the entire document on the same page instead of pausing after each page I haven't tried OW yet, though OW is the same But, the definition of broken is relative Pageview requires DSC compliant PostScript files, in order to stop at page breaks I don't consider that broken I say that any program that puts out a PostScript file that isn't DSC compliant is broken harvard ucbvax uwvax astroatc ftms brown or uu psi com ftms brown rutgers INTERNET or ftms brown astroatc UUCP cs wisc edu